      "text": "noisy neighbor",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "noisy neighbor",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "hcu8dwJbhuEI9_bWXQhCW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 196,
      "y": 766,
      "width": 724.3995361328125,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aN",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1144651366,
      "version": 284,
      "versionNonce": 742467578,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1784304552019,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Linux kernal has a feature called \"Namespaces\"\n    - you can use this to isolate running applications from each other \n        - memory, processor, virtual file systems, even TCP port remappint.\n        - super cool, super powerful, super super linux neckbeard level stuff.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Linux kernal has a feature called \"Namespaces\"\n    - you can use this to isolate running applications from each other \n        - memory, processor, virtual file systems, even TCP port remappint.\n        - super cool, super powerful, super super linux neckbeard level stuff.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "lRwxYwte0OYGtyavglxxS",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 215,
      "y": 920,
      "width": 833.5194702148438,
      "height": 475,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1967350394,
      "version": 493,
      "versionNonce": 1857022566,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1784304820054,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why don't we make this easier?\n\n- Make declarative way for the an application to set up the namespace stuff.\n    - can also be overriden on the server, etc.\n\nDockerfile\n\n    - has our code + all the stuff from the \"kernel up\" that you need.\n\n\n- distribution in docker files\n\nThe dependencies in a container are \"layered\", each layer relying on the layer below it.\n\nWhen a dependency changes, that layer and all layers above it have to be replaced.\n\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why don't we make this easier?\n\n- Make declarative way for the an application to set up the namespace stuff.\n    - can also be overriden on the server, etc.\n\nDockerfile\n\n    - has our code + all the stuff from the \"kernel up\" that you need.\n\n\n- distribution in docker files\n\nThe dependencies in a container are \"layered\", each layer relying on the layer below it.\n\nWhen a dependency changes, that layer and all layers above it have to be replaced.\n\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
